-- Bank of East Asia, Wing Hang Ratings Lowered at HSBC on Yuan `Overplayed'
-- Shiyin Chen
-- 2010-08-02T00:25:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/bank-of-east-asia-wing-hang-ratings-lowered-at-hsbc-on-yuan-overplayed-.html

          
          
             Bank of East Asia Ltd., Wing Hang
Bank Ltd. and Dah Sing Financial Group had their ratings lowered
by HSBC Holdings Plc, who said the hype over the yuan business
and mergers and acquisitions may be “overplayed.”  
 Bank of East Asia and Wing Hang were cut to “underweight”
from “neutral” and Dah Sing Financial’s rating was lowered to
“neutral” from “overweight.”  
